LiZnPO$_{4}$ has been observed in a variety of structures. We list those which have known crystal structures: \begin{itemize} \item \href{current_web_home_dir/AB4CD_mC224_9_8a_32a_8a_8a-001}{$\alpha$-LiZnPO$_{4}$} \item \href{current_web_home_dir/AB4CD_oP28_33_a_4a_a_a-001}{$\delta_{1}$-LiZnPO$_{4}$}, and \item \href{current_web_home_dir/AB4CD_hR42_146_2b_8b_2b_2b-001}{rhombohedral LiZnPO$_{4}$} (this structure). \end{itemize} ~ \vspace{-.25in} 
 (Bu, 1996) note that this structure is very close to \href{current_web_home_dir/A2B4C_hR42_148_2f_4f_f-001}{phenakite (Be$_{2}$SiO$_{4}$, $S1_{3}$)}, the main difference being the lack of an inversion site. 
 Hexagonal settings of this structure can be obtained with the option {\tt --hex}.
